16/06/2004
TIRANA, Albania - According to local press reports Tuesday (15 June), President Alfred Moisiu is quoted as saying he is not pleased with the politics surrounding the adoption of the property bill. 
He implied that parliament should reconsider some of the articles in the law, which was adopted on 8 June with only the ruling Socialist Party present. 
The OSCE also has been critical, calling for consensus in adopting the key document. 
(Albanian Daily News - 16/06/04)
